rmk: A single individual was heard daily for over a month during March-April 2019 period at the location. Calling would generally start around 20:00 hours, and sometimes go on till the middle of the night. Occasionally the owl was even heard early in the morning. As this is the start of the summer, and breeding season for several of the resident species of the place, this could be a call to attract a mate. Post this month-long observation, the species was heard occasionally, and a pair was seen on a few occasions as well.

This recording is an unusual call of the brown hawk owl(Ninox scutulata) from the campus of KFRI, Peechi, Thrissur. The location is a patch of forest with rigorous human  presence but very near to the Peechi-Vazhani wildlife sanctuary.  The uploaded recording is a merged recording of different calls of the same birds at various time point taken using smartphones ,long gaps of noises has been removed, the audio is unedited else wise.  This call is very distinct and different that of the normal call of hawk owl. The pair of Owls were making these calls one after another sitting at different trees close by.
The audio was recorded by myself and Dr Riju P Nair.

For further information contact: shineraj263@gmail.com

We used playback of the brown hawk owl and got a good response. The owl was responding in a tree in thick bush. We used a rhino and elephant track to get closer (not particularly a wise idea) however we went anyway and managed to record and view well the brown hawk owl. Surprisingly the mottled wood owl that we were also trying to find also responded to the call of the brown hawk owl.
Recorded with iPhone 4s. Short excerpt from tail end of vocalization bout. Signal amplified significantly.
